{
  "doc_id": "16008",
  "text": "A simple solution to varying time-delay systems is to use an event-based version of the standard proportional-integralderivative (PID) controller [CITATION_1] , though the stability analysis of the closed-loop system becomes hard due to the time-variant controller. Another alternative is to rely on the time-based PID controller, but detune it with appropriate methods that provide robustness to the delays [CITATION_2] , [CITATION_3] . In this case, the stability can be guaranteed by the use of simple stability criteria such as [CITATION_4] .",
